@article{Imai__JCP_2003,
abstract = {Statistical mechanical expressions for the partial molar volume (PMV) and the partial molar compressibility (PMC) of a solute molecule with internal degrees of freedom are derived. The equilibrium PMV is expressed simply by the conformational ensemble average of PMV. The equilibrium PMC consists of two terms: the conformational ensemble average of PMC and the mean square fluctuation of PMV along conformational axis. As an illustrative application of the theory, the equilibrium PMV and PMC of butane in aqueous solution are calculated from the relations, in which the thermodynamic quantities of each conformer appearing in the relations are obtained by the reference interaction site model theory. The conformational ensemble average of PMC is the predominant contribution to the equilibrium PMC in this particular example. Possibility of shedding light on the protein conformation in terms of PMV and PMC is discussed. (C) 2003 American Institute of Physics.},
