abstract = {The applicability of the reference interaction site model (RISM) to calculating the free energy of hydration of a set of 63 bioactive compounds presented in the work of J.P. Guthrie (Phys. Chem. B. 2009. V. 443. P. 4504) is tested. The performance of four different formulas for calculating the hydration free energy within the framework of the RISM, KH, HNCB, GF, and PW, is compared. Based on a training set of 32 compounds, the results are parameterized with corrections for the excluded volume and the number of atoms of each type in the molecule. It is shown that, for CHELPG charges, the parameterization predicts the results with a root-mean-square deviation from the experimental data of RMSD = 1.9 kcal/mol, a prediction almost 1.5-fold better than the results of parameterization without the use of the RISM.},
